â€¢ Updated footsteps sounds in Lamplit Stones and in Adabana Gardens linked to the Maiko effect.

â€¢ Fixed an issue when going back from Rainy Apartments to Virtual City could place the player in a wall.

â€¢ Fixed a collision issue in Virtual City and adjusted video events behaviours.

â€¢ Updated FC Caverns, Virtual City and Rainy Apartments to use shorter sound effects.

â€¢ Changed the transition between Neon Caves and Static Labyrinth.

â€¢ Changed the interaction with Aojiru in the Hospital to use a Common Event.

â€¢ Fixed an issue with the track 521A in the Sound Room.

â€¢ Made various changes to Common Events.

feeds.content: R: 167 / I: 7                                                          Rust Thread>inb4 tranny language not gonna botherWhy is there no Rust thread yet? I have taught it myself after Go and to me it feels like it allows me to write concurrent code much easier and giving me more control over how I wanna implement it (threads, channels or async). The learning resources also feel like the best I've ever dealt with, there's an official learning book, there's "Rust by example", the standard library docs always provide examples too and there's a million more good things I can say about it. Up until now I haven't ran into any significant problems with the language unlike Go (https://fasterthanli.me/articles/i-want-off-mr-golangs-wild-ride) and I think in the future it will entirely replace C++. Has lainon tried Rust yet?

Contributing Authors: Kontentsu
Release Date: 2022/10/06




â€¢ Added the Mossy Stone Area, accessible from the Red Streetlight World and the Geometry World.

â€¢ Added the Desolate Park, accessible from the Mossy Stone Area.

â€¢ Added the Red Strings Maze, accessible from the Desolate Park.

â€¢ Added the Budding Life World, accessible from the Red Strings Maze.

â€¢ Added the Funky Dusky Hall, accessible from the Budding Life World.

â€¢ Added the Drowsy Forest, accessible under specific conditions from the Hot Air Balloon World.

â€¢ Added the  Oil Puddle World, accessible under specific conditions from The Nexus.

â€¢ Added a connection to Digital Forest from  Oil Puddle World.

â€¢ Replaced the connection to Digital Forest from Geometry World with a connection to Mossy Stone Area.

â€¢ Fixed an issue in Pudding World where the fire could be extinguished while it should not.

â€¢ Fixed an issue in the Unknown Child's Room and in the Dessert Fields.

â€¢ Added tracks 68C, 214D, 284D, 307D, 576A, 577A and 578A to the Sound Room.



Patch 1 / Contributing Authors: Kontentsu
Release Date: 2022/10/06




â€¢ Fixed an issue in the Digital Forest linked to the previous connection to Geometry World.

â€¢ Fixed a collision issue in the Drowsy Forest.

â€¢ Updated graphics of Obsidian Plains.

â€¢ Fixed an issue with the chipset that lead into graphics issues in the Bright Forest and The Second Nexus.

â€¢ Merged tracks 476 and 576A and moved down tracks 578A and 579A.



Patch 2 / Contributing Authors: qxy
Release Date: 2022/10/06




â€¢ Updated the FC Caverns:
â€¢ Adjusted the section of Color Cubes World to make the area easier and shorter.

â€¢ Moved Windswept Scarlet Sands connection from the section of Color Cubes World to Static Labyrinth.

â€¢ Fixed a collision issue that could occur when switching from a short effect to a bigger effect (Fairy to Bike for example) allowing the player to walk through walls.

â€¢ Fixed an issue where the color could be changed while using the Bike, Marginal effect or by falling.

â€¢ Updated various things linked to collision.


â€¢ Adjusted the chair in Home Within Nowhere to be able to sit on it while wearing a hat.

â€¢ Fixed an issue with the transition from the Pure White Lands to the White Garden sub-area.

â€¢ Updated footsteps sounds in Lamplit Stones and in Adabana Gardens linked to the Maiko effect.

â€¢ Fixed an issue when going back from Rainy Apartments to Virtual City could place the player in a wall.

â€¢ Fixed a collision issue in Virtual City and adjusted video events behaviours.

â€¢ Updated FC Caverns, Virtual City and Rainy Apartments to use shorter sound effects.

â€¢ Changed the transition between Neon Caves and Static Labyrinth.

â€¢ Changed the interaction with Aojiru in the Hospital to use a Common Event.

â€¢ Fixed an issue with the track 521A in the Sound Room.

â€¢ Made various changes to Common Events.
